  "title": "Automation Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key\nResponsibilities:</strong></p><p>·  Develop and execute long-term automation strategies, identifying manual processes\nsuitable for conversion into automated workflows.</p><p>·  Manage and mentor a multidisciplinary team, including automation engineers, RPA\ndevelopers, and technicians.</p><p>·  Oversee the end-to-end lifecycle of automation projects, including budgeting, resource\nallocation, and meeting strict deadlines.</p><p>·  Lead the design of mechanical or electrical systems (e.g., PLCs, SCADA, robotics)\nand manage ongoing maintenance and troubleshooting</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>·  Minimum Degree  in Mechatronics, Robotics, Electrical Engineering or equivalent.<br /><br />.  Knowledge of PLC programming, industrial robotics, and CAD software (AutoCAD,\n   SolidWorks).<br /><br />.  Taking ownership of results and actions<br /><br />.   Requires 5–10 years of experience in automation or engineering, with at\n     least 3 years in a management or lead role</p>",
